@Immutable
final class MomentImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements Stopwatch.Moment

This class represents a "moment", with a long integer value from System.nanoTime() and a String title. A MomentImpl has accessors whenGet() and titleGet(). This class represents a "moment", with a long integer value from System.nanoTime() and a String title. A MomentImpl has accessors whenGet() and titleGet(). MomentImpl has its own toString() method, which return the two values in (something like) this format: "%012d\t%s", where the first value is for when and the second value is for title. A Moment object becomes visible to a caller only as an element in the List returned from momentsRetrieve().
